%20logs%20from%20the%20city%20of%20Las%20Vegas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20two%20separate%20occasions%20in%20October%202021%20and%20February%202022%2C%20Las%20Vegas%20city%20officials%20knocked%20on%20the%20door%2C%20according%20to%20government%20logs.%20The%20people%20who%20answered%20said%20they%20were%20renting%20the%20property%20through%20Airbnb%2C%20the%20logs%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETao%20was%20issued%20%242%2C132%20in%20fines%20from%20the%20February%202022%20incident%20%E2%80%94%20%24500%20per%20day%20for%20the%20four%20days%20the%20alleged%20Airbnb%20guest%20said%20they%20were%20staying%20in%20the%20home%2C%20plus%20additional%20fees%2C%20according%20to%20city%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETao%20said%20he%20believed%20that%2C%20after%20the%20February%202022%20incident%2C%20his%20tenant%20had%20stopped%20renting%20out%20his%20property%20on%20Airbnb%20and%20the%20issue%20was%20resolved.%20He%20claimed%20he%20was%20unable%20to%20confront%20the%20tenant%20directly%20because%20he%20was%20managing%20the%20property%20remotely%20from%20Oregon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tenant%20vacated%20the%20property%20in%20September%202023%2C%20and%20a%20cleaner%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20premises%20to%20tidy%20up%2C%20Tao%20said.%20Stuck%20to%20the%20window%20was%20a%20notice%20of%20a%20%24180%2C000%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20shocked.%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20was%20going%20on.%20I%20thought%20it%20might%20be%20fraud%2C%26quot%3B%20Tao%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20we%20go%20from%20%242%2C000%20to%20%24180%2C000%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e3230253-bc23-4b29-93f2-64953a4e16eb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELas%20Vegas%20is%20cracking%20down%20on%20Airbnb%20hosts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20Tao%20asked%20the%20Las%20Vegas%20City%20Council%20to%20reconsider%20the%20fine%2C%20but%20lawmakers%20unanimously%20upheld%20the%20decision%20by%20a%20vote%20of%207-0%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reviewjournal.com%2Fne